3 PCA analysis using 4-cell (S3) and 8-cell (S4) data

#Create sample files table
sampleFiles <- c("El.bam","Ep.bam", "Er.bam","en.bam", "g.bam", "ml.bam","mr.bam","Mv.bam","Eml.bam","Emr.bam","Epen.bam","Mavg.bam")
lineage <- factor(c(rep(c('Ect'),times=3),"End","Germ",rep(c('Mes'),times=3),c("Eml","Emr","Epen","Mavg")),
                  levels = c("Ect","End","Germ","Mes","Eml","Emr","Epen","Mavg"))
blastomere <- factor(c("El","Ep", "Er","en", "g", "ml","mr","Mav","Eml","Emr","Epen","Mavg"),
                     levels = c("El","Ep", "Er","en", "g", "ml","mr","Mav","Eml","Emr","Epen","Mavg"))

sampleTable <- data.frame(sampleName = sampleFiles, condition = blastomere)

#Load count matrix into DeSEQ and plotPCA
s3s4_data <- merge(stageS4_exonCounts$counts %>% as.data.frame(),stageS3_exonCounts$counts %>% as.data.frame(),by=0) #%>% as.matrix()

dds_s3s4 <- DESeqDataSetFromMatrix(countData = s3s4_data[,sampleFiles], #Change order to match conditions
                              colData = sampleTable,
                              design = ~condition)
dds_s3s4 <- dds_s3s4 %>% vst %>% plotPCA(ntop=1000,returnData=T) #+ geom_point(aes(shape=rep(19,times=12))) #+ geom_text(aes(label=colnames())

s3s4_PCA <- dds_s3s4 %>% mutate(lineage = factor(c(rep(c('Ect'),times=3),"End","Germ",rep(c('Mes'),times=3),c("Eml","Emr","Epen","Mavg")),
                                      levels = c("Ect","End","Germ","Mes","Eml","Emr","Epen","Mavg")),
                    stage = factor(c(rep(c('8-cell'),times=8),c(rep(c('4-cell'),times=4))),levels= c("4-cell","8-cell"))) %>%
  mutate(blastomere = factor(condition,levels = c("Eml","Emr","Epen","Mavg","El","Ep", "Er","en", "g", "ml","mr","Mav"))) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x=PC1,y=PC2,color=blastomere,shape=stage)) + geom_point(size=3) +
  scale_color_manual(values=c("orange2","forestgreen","red","blue","maroon4","maroon3", #Colors by lineage
     "maroon2","orangered","magenta","salmon4","salmon3","cyan4")) + #Color by blastomere                                 
  theme_bw()

4 TPM values estimated using TPM Calculator

  less ../tpm_counts/run_tpmCalculator.sh

#!/bin/bash 

in=/drives/raid/AboobakerLab/data/bams/phaw/hisat/bams_8cell_embryos
annotation=/drives/ssd1/manuel/phaw/2022_analysis/annotation/protein_coding_genes/transdecoder/unigenes/transcripts_cdhit_0.95.fa.transdecoder.genome_unigenes.gtf
bam_files=$(ls $in | grep ".bam$")

for i in $bam_files; do
    f=$(basename $i .bam)
    
    echo "Analysis started for ${f}"
        TPMCalculator -v -g $annotation -k gene_id -t transcript_id -p -b ${in}/${i}
    echo "**** TPM values calculated for $f ****"
done
#Open TPM counts - 4-cell stage

#Open TPM counts - 8-cell stage

6 mRNA dynamics during 4_to_8-cell transition

6.1 mRNA fate for Mavg daugther blastomeres Mav and g

#Mav vs g mRNA dynamics during S3-S4 transition
#Set filter to plot genes having at least 3TPM in the mother cell
mavg_TPM_filt <- allTPM_df_s3 %>% filter(Mavg >= 3)  %>% pull(gene_id) 

mavg_RNAsegreg <- s3s4_TPMdata  %>% mutate_if(is.numeric, ~. + 0.001)  %>% #replace(is.na(.), 0) %>%
  filter(gene_id %in% mavg_TPM_filt, Mav != "NA", g != "NA") %>% 
  mutate(mav_mavg = round(Mav/Mavg,2),g_mavg = round(g/Mavg,2)) %>% rowwise() %>%
  mutate(Class = ifelse(between(mav_mavg,0.5,35) & between(g_mavg,0,0.5) & between(mav_mavg/g_mavg,1.1,200),"Mav_localised",
                        ifelse(between(g_mavg,0.5,35) & between(mav_mavg,0,0.5) &between(g_mavg/mav_mavg,1.1,200),"g_localised",
                               ifelse(between(g_mavg,0,0.5) & between(mav_mavg/g_mavg,1.1,200),"g_deadenylation",
                                      ifelse(between(mav_mavg,0,0.5) & between(g_mavg/mav_mavg,1.1,200),"mav_deadenylation",
                                             ifelse(between(mav_mavg/g_mavg,0.9,1.1) & mav_mavg >= 0.47 & g_mavg >= 0.47,"Sym_polyadenylation",
                                                    ifelse(between(mav_mavg/g_mavg,0.9,1.1) & mav_mavg <= 0.5 & g_mavg <= 0.5,"Sym_deadenylation",
                                                           ifelse(between(g_mavg/mav_mavg,1.1,200),"gAsym_polyadenylation",
                                                                  ifelse(between(mav_mavg/g_mavg,1.1,200),"MavAsym_polyadenylation","NA"))))))))) %>% tibble() %>%
  mutate(Class = factor(Class,levels = c("NA","Mav_localised","g_localised","g_deadenylation","mav_deadenylation","Sym_deadenylation","Sym_polyadenylation","gAsym_polyadenylation","MavAsym_polyadenylation"))) %>%  arrange(Class) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x=mav_mavg,y=g_mavg,colour = Class,name=Gene_Symbol))+ geom_point(shape=19,size=1.5,alpha=0.75) + #Names can be changed to Human (Hsa_id)
  scale_x_continuous(trans = log10_trans(),breaks = c(seq(0,0.5, 0.25),1,2,3,4,5,10,20),labels = c(seq(0,0.5, 0.25),1,2,3,4,5,10,20)) +
  scale_y_continuous(trans = log10_trans(),breaks = c(seq(0,0.5, 0.25),1,2,3,4,5,10,20),labels = c(seq(0,0.5, 0.25),1,2,3,4,5,10,20)) +
  scale_color_brewer(palette = "Paired") + xlab("Mav/Mavg TPM") + ylab("g/Mavg TPM") +
  guides(colour = guide_legend(override.aes = list(size=5))) +
  theme(axis.title = element_text(size = 18),legend.position = "right", legend.text = element_text(size=10),legend.title =  element_text(size=11),
        legend.key.size = unit(0.5, 'cm'),axis.text = element_text(size = 10),
        plot.title = element_text(size=20, hjust = 0.5)) + labs(color='mRNA fate') + theme_bw()
